snippet.textDisplay:
I believe Ghost is alive. Episode 13 didn’t show him dead. There was an ambulance near by. When Tommy was leaning over him , he lifted his eyes up to the balcony gesturing for Tommy to look up. I don’t believe the shooter was there. His eye language said to me ‘Tommy, I have a plan”. Tommy sneered at the figure on the balcony out of anger and pain. Tommy knew his body language. He owns an ambulatory service and Tommy expected the shooting to happen. 
 
After degrading the likes of Tommy, Tate and getting in the way of the drug plight that Tariq is in with the Italians, there is no way Ghost a wealthy drug kingpin & club owner also who have eliminated other drug mobs would not have the instincts that he would be targeted at a big political event after going public. And, to not have a gun nor vest on in his night club alone? Neither Ghost nor James St. Patrick could be that Naïve!!!
 
Tate hands are firing the gun (may not be at the shooting scene), they are the same hands at 0.16 telling Dre “You only have 1 shot”.
Tate is speaking at a church, the people are clapping. That is not a funeral. Ramona is in that same event, a man behind her (left) is clapping, and she is wearing a green dress and not black. 
 
In his way are: Tommy (I think they gave each other what they wanted though),Tate, Stein/Stern (straddles the fence between he & Tate) and Saxe (I believe Saxe is in his pocket though)… I hope St. Patrick don’t give Tommy up!!!  I believe Tate has a few guns pointed at Ghost!!!
 
I think Saxe made the plot shot, Tommy will be framed for Ghost’s murder plot. The recording copy of Tommy from Proctor’s flash drive is in Blanca’s possession, and he’s aware of it. All eyes are on Tommy , he goes on a rampage snubs  Saxe and Tasha. Blanca has enough evidence to put those special handcuffs on him.  The Italians take him out. St. Patrick get’s a clean background check.

snippet.textDisplay:
My theory: As much as we want to think Tariq killed Ghost, I think there’s a big plot twist to his murder, and Tariq is not the killer... I don’t think 50 would end the series with a predictable finale. It’s too easy. Tariq, along with Tommy, Tasha, Dre, etc been talking about taking this man out all for a few seasons now. There’s no way he’d kill off a character who practically made the show without giving us a jaw dropper.

I think, Tariq DID INDEED go to Truth to kill Ghost, but someone else (Romana, I believe) got to him first and Tariq witnessed it; or maybe he arrived after Ghost was shot.

Ghost was looking up the entire time and suddenly got shook by someone appearing over that balcony. I think Tariq looked and Ghost got scared for Tariq because he knew that Tommy would’ve assumed it was him and that’s why Ghost said to let it go.


Reason why I believe Ramona shot Ghost is because when she and Angela’s sister was speaking, she had that cold look in her eye and tone when she said, “sometimes people are just unstoppable” maybe indicating that no one who is a known enemy to Ghost can stop him, but she can because he’s already falling for her and suspects little. As far as her motive goes? I don’t know....
